libmad
-------------------------------------------
MAD (libmad) is a high-quality MPEG audio decoder. It currently supports
MPEG-1 and the MPEG-2 extension to Lower Sampling Frequencies, as well 
as the so-called MPEG 2.5 format. All three audio layers (Layer I, Layer 
II, and Layer III a.k.a. MP3) are fully implemented.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-1.5.25-15

Build requirements:
  autoconf2.5-2.61-1
  automake1.9-1.9.6-2
  binutils-20080523-1
  cygport-0.3.11-1
  gawk-3.1.6-1
  gcc-core-3.4.4-3
  libtool-2.2.2-2
  make-3.81-1
  sed-4.1.5-2

Canonical homepage:
  http://www.underbit.com/products/mad/

Canonical download:
  ftp://ftp.mars.org/pub/mpeg/
  http://downloads.sourceforge.net/mad/

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  unpack libmad-0.15.1b-X-src.tar.bz2
    if you use setup to install this src package, it will be
	 unpacked under /usr/src automatically
  cd /usr/src
  cygport ./libmad-0.15.1b-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/libmad-0.15.1b-X-src.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/libmad-0.15.1b-X.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/libmad-devel-0.15.1b-X.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/libmad0-0.15.1b-X.tar.bz2

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary packages:

(libmad0)
  /usr/bin/cygmad-0.dll
  /usr/share/doc/libmad-0.15.1b/CHANGES
  /usr/share/doc/libmad-0.15.1b/COPYING
  /usr/share/doc/libmad-0.15.1b/CREDITS
  /usr/share/doc/libmad-0.15.1b/INSTALL
  /usr/share/doc/libmad-0.15.1b/README
  /usr/share/doc/libmad-0.15.1b/TODO

(libmad-devel)
  /usr/include/mad.h
  /usr/lib/libmad.a
  /usr/lib/libmad.dll.a
  /usr/lib/libmad.la
  /usr/lib/pkgconfig/mad.pc

